parties.raw_snippet: THIS MARINE TRANSPORTATION AGREEMENT (this “Agreement”) is executed this 23rd day of December, 2003, by and between Martin Operating Partnership L.P., a Delaware limited partnership (“Owner”), and Midstream Fuel Service LLC, an Alabama limited liability company (“Charterer”), in order to evidence the agreement of such parties with respect to Owner’s provision of marine transportation services with respect to #2 fuel oil and high sulfur diesel on board its marine vessels under the following terms and conditions.
parties.reasoning: The opening paragraph expressly names the two contracting entities, Martin Operating Partnership L.P. and Midstream Fuel Service LLC, and identifies them as the parties to this Agreement (with defined roles “Owner” and “Charterer”).

contract_type.raw_snippet: THIS MARINE TRANSPORTATION AGREEMENT (this “Agreement”) is executed this 23rd day of December, 2003, by and between Martin Operating Partnership L.P., a Delaware limited partnership (“Owner”), and Midstream Fuel Service LLC, an Alabama limited liability company (“Charterer”), in order to evidence the agreement of such parties with respect to Owner’s provision of marine transportation services with respect to #2 fuel oil and high sulfur diesel on board its marine vessels under the following terms and conditions.
contract_type.reasoning: The core obligation is Owner providing marine transportation services for #2 fuel oil and high sulfur diesel and Charterer paying fees for that service. The title and substantive provisions (e.g., Section 2 and Section 3) confirm this is fundamentally an agreement for transportation services.

notice_period.raw_snippet: This Agreement will automatically renew for successive one year terms (each a “Renewal Term”, and together with the Initial Term, the “Term”), unless either Charterer or Owner elects not to renew this Agreement by providing the other party with written notice of such election 30 days prior to the expiration of the Initial Term or Renewal Term, as applicable, at which point this Agreement will automatically terminate.
notice_period.reasoning: This sentence sets the mechanism to prevent automatic renewal: a party must provide written notice 30 days prior to the expiration of the Initial Term or Renewal Term to elect not to renew.

expiration_date.raw_snippet: The initial term of this Agreement shall be for 3 years (the “Initial Term”) commencing on the date first set forth above (the “Commencement Date”) and ending on the 3rd anniversary of the Commencement Date.
expiration_date.reasoning: Section 1 specifies the Initial Term is three years and explicitly states it ends on the 3rd anniversary of the Commencement Date; this is the relative expiration description for the initial term.
expiration_date.normalized_value: 3 years (ending on the 3rd anniversary of the Commencement Date)

renewal_term.raw_snippet: This Agreement will automatically renew for successive one year terms (each a “Renewal Term", and together with the Initial Term, the “Term”), unless either Charterer or Owner elects not to renew this Agreement by providing the other party with written notice of such election 30 days prior to the expiration of the Initial Term or Renewal Term, as applicable, at which point this Agreement will automatically terminate.
renewal_term.reasoning: The Agreement specifies automatic renewal for successive one year terms unless timely notice is given, so each Renewal Term is one year and renewals are automatic.

agreement_date.raw_snippet: THIS MARINE TRANSPORTATION AGREEMENT (this “Agreement”) is executed this 23rd day of December, 2003, by and between Martin Operating Partnership L.P., a Delaware limited partnership (“Owner”), and Midstream Fuel Service LLC, an Alabama limited liability company (“Charterer”), ...
agreement_date.reasoning: The opening sentence states the agreement is "executed this 23rd day of December, 2003," which is the signing/making date.

effective_date.raw_snippet: The initial term of this Agreement shall be for 3 years (the “Initial Term”) commencing on the date first set forth above (the “Commencement Date”) and ending on the 3rd anniversary of the Commencement Date.
effective_date.reasoning: The agreement defines the Initial Term as commencing "on the date first set forth above," which refers back to the execution/signing date (the 23rd day of December, 2003). Therefore the effective/commencement date is the agreement date.

governing_law.raw_snippet: This Agreement shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of the State of Texas.
governing_law.reasoning: Section 8 is the governing law clause and explicitly names the State of Texas as the jurisdiction whose laws govern the Agreement.
